<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/407: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-25T15:00:00-06:00">January 25, 1934—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4. The Foreign Office informed me that the Governments of Guatemala,
                            Honduras, and Nicaragua have recognized the present regime in Salvador
                            today. The recognitions were granted by telegrams from the Foreign
                            Ministers of those countries to the Salvadoran Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McCafferty</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>